POLICE arrested three teenagers on Monday afternoon for armed robbery and possession of an unlicensed firearm. The 16-year-olds were bust in Pretoria West in Tshwane. Constable Sibongile Vuma said cops were stopped by an unknown man who told them three young men had just robbed two women of their cellphones. She said the suspects were spotted while buying items at a local shop. “Police approached the suspects, searched them and found an unlicensed firearm and two cellphones belonging to the victims. “The suspects were arrested and detained at Pretoria West Police Station.” Vuma said the suspects were due to appear in the Pretoria Magistrates Court soon for a bail hearing.